o decide whether to modify the script for auto-discovery or stick with a static scan list. However, the user asks for every repo to be included in the scanning list.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering repo discovery methods**\\n\\nI’m thinking it might be more efficient to update the `discover_git_repos` function to automatically include all repos with an origin or upstream while possibly leaving `repos.json` empty or auto-generated. While using an explicit configuration is easier, new repos won't be scanned in the future. The user's request for \\\"全量的仓库都加入\\\" points to needing the current list. It could also make sense to generate a report of included repos and check the plist for the scheduling aspect.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"我补看一下自动调度时间，然后就写清单。顺手把嵌套重复仓去掉，避免日报重复。","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0faca0e75e9e48550169cda9d4ec28819aac35243eba5bf49f\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_GfhndunE4gafmWu6L4ydV27b|fc_0faca0e75e9e48550169cda9dd92c4819aa919aca87c3ac7a5","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/Users/ling/Library/LaunchAgents/com.ling.github-repo-monitor.plist","limit":240},"partialJson":"{\"file\":\"/Users/ling/Library/LaunchAgents/com.ling.github-repo-monitor.plist\",\"limit\":240}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Q1UqsAPHZCUKmwOfErsfUKT7|fc_0faca0e75e9e48550169cda9dd96c4819a8e2acf9cdb9aa8c4","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport json, subprocess\nworkspace = Path('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace')\nroots = [workspace/'quant_projects', workspace/'other_projects', workspace/'openclaw_projects', workspace/'apps', workspace/'skills', workspace/'vendor', workspace/'SideLinker-Home']\nrepos = []\nfor root in roots:\n    if not root.exists():\n        continue\n    candidates = []\n    if root.is_dir() and (root/'.git').exists():\n        candidates.append(root)\n    if root.is_dir():\n        candidates += [p for p in root.iterdir() if p.is_dir()]\n    for repo in candidates:\n        r = subprocess.run(['git','-C',str(repo),'rev-parse','--is-inside-work-tree'], capture_output=True, text=True)\n        if r.returncode != 0 or r.stdout.strip() != 'true':\n            continue\n        rr = subprocess.run(['git','-C',str(repo),'rev-parse','--show-toplevel'], capture_output=True, text=True)\n        if rr.returncode != 0:\n            continue\n        top = rr.stdout.strip()\n        def get(remote):\n            x = subprocess.run(['git','-C',str(repo),'remote','get-url',remote], capture_output=True, text=True)\n            return x.stdout.strip() if x.returncode == 0 else ''\n        origin = get('origin')\n        upstream = get('upstream')\n        if not (origin or upstream):\n            continue\n        repos.append({'config_path': str(repo), 'git_top': top, 'origin': origin, 'upstream': upstream})\n# de-duplicate nested duplicates: if config_path is child of another config_path and same git_top, drop child\nrepos = sorted(repos, key=lambda x: (len(x['config_path']), x['config_path']))\nkept = []\nfor item in repos:\n    cp = Path(item['config_path'])\n    dup = False\n    for existing in kept:\n        ep = Path(existing['config_path'])\n        if item['git_top'] == existing['git_top'] and (cp == ep or ep in cp.parents):\n            dup = True\n            break\n    if not dup:\n        kept.append(item)\nprint(json.dumps(kept, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\nPY","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":120},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"python3 - <<'PY'\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nimport json, subprocess\\nworkspace = Path('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace')\\nroots = [workspace/'quant_projects', workspace/'other_projects', workspace/'openclaw_projects', workspace/'apps', workspace/'skills', workspace/'vendor', workspace/'SideLinker-Home']\\nrepos = []\\nfor root in roots:\\n    if not root.exists():\\n        continue\\n    candidates = []\\n    if root.is_dir() and (root/'.git').exists():\\n        candidates.append(root)\\n    if root.is_dir():\\n        candidates += [p for p in root.iterdir() if p.is_dir()]\\n    for repo in candidates:\\n        r = subprocess.run(['git','-C',str(repo),'rev-parse','--is-inside-work-tree'], capture_output=True, text=True)\\n        if r.returncode != 0 or r.stdout.strip() != 'true':\\n            continue\\n        rr = subprocess.run(['git','-C',str(repo),'rev-parse','--show-toplevel'], capture_output=True, text=True)\\n        if rr.returncode != 0:\\n            continue\\n        top = rr.stdout.strip()\\n        def get(remote):\\n            x = subprocess.run(['git','-C',str(repo),'remote','get-url',remote], capture_output=True, text=True)\\n            return x.stdout.strip() if x.returncode == 0 else ''\\n        origin = get('origin')\\n        upstream = get('upstream')\\n        if not (origin or upstream):\\n            continue\\n        repos.append({'config_path': str(repo), 'git_top': top, 'origin': origin, 'upstream': upstream})\\n# de-duplicate nested duplicates: if config_path is child of another config_path and same git_top, drop child\\nrepos = sorted(repos, key=lambda x: (len(x['config_path']), x['config_path']))\\nkept = []\\nfor item in repos:\\n    cp = Path(item['config_path'])\\n    dup = False\\n    for existing in kept:\\n        ep = Path(existing['config_path'])\\n        if item['git_top'] == existing['git_top'] and (cp == ep or ep in cp.parents):\\n            dup = True\\n            break\\n    if not dup:\\n        kept.append(item)\\nprint(json.dumps(kept, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\\nPY\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace\",\"timeout\":120}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":19131,"output":1176,"cacheRead":116736,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":137043,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775086021626,"responseId":"resp_0faca0e75e9e48550169cda9c6bb00819a8a57250b476d994e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1e16b390","parentId":"76b531fa","timestamp":"2026-04-01T23:27:26.067Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_GfhndunE4gafmWu6L4ydV27b|fc_0faca0e75e9e48550169cda9dd92c4819aa919aca87c3ac7a5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC \"-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN\" \"http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd\">\n<plist version=\"1.0\">\n<dict>\n    <key>Label</key>\n    <string>com.ling.github-repo-monitor</string>\n    <key>ProgramArguments</key>\n    <array>\n        <string>/usr/local/bin/python3</string>\n        <string>/Users/ling/.openclaw/skills/github-repo-monitor/scripts/check_updates.py</string>\n    </array>\n    <key>WorkingDirectory</key>\n    <string>/Users/ling/.openclaw/skills/github-repo-monitor</string>\n    <key>StandardOutPath</key>\n    <string>/Users/ling/.openclaw/skills/github-repo-monitor/logs/check_updates.log</string>\n    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>\n    <string>/Users/ling/.openclaw/skills/github-repo-monitor/logs/check_updates.err</string>\n    <key>StartCalendarInterval</key>\n    <dict>\n        <key>Hour</key><integer>9</integer>\n        <key>Minute</key><integer>0</integer>\n    </dict>\n    <key>RunAtLoad</key>\n    <false/>\n</dict>\n</plist>\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775086046063}}
