{"type":"message","id":"02979d67","parentId":"3d343e40","timestamp":"2026-04-02T01:30:58.452Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b53e8418a58a4c4961d964020f47\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_968a615509dc191f04220e18cda67080\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"oc_8a819be3a90d35b8d0a2d5c1f4642b22\",\n  \"sender\": \"张玲\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-04-02 09:05 GMT+8\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"oc_8a819be3a90d35b8d0a2d5c1f4642b22\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"张玲 (ou_968a615509dc191f04220e18cda67080)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_968a615509dc191f04220e18cda67080\",\n  \"name\": \"张玲\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b53e8418a58a4c4961d964020f47]\n张玲: daily_stock_analysis_upgrade_preview、daily_stock_analysis_upstream都是源于daily_stock_analysis，下次就不用播报这个仓库的更新情况了。上游已更新，本地没更新的，需要做出判断：是否值得更新，在仓库检查任务里面一并播报。<at user_id=\"ou_c209a91ac6a25a1ba09bc1eb91985a53\">coding agent</at>\n\n[System: The content may include mention tags in the form <at user_id=\"...\">name</at>. Treat these as real mentions of Feishu entities (users or bots).]\n[System: If user_id is \"ou_eaa82a8ab7584770b4b4974610c16e80\", that mention refers to you.]"}],"timestamp":1775093458445}}
{"type":"message","id":"6485933f","parentId":"02979d67","timestamp":"2026-04-02T01:32:02.126Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering report updates**\n\nI need to continue making adjustments, possibly providing proof in the same turn. Editing the configuration to remove two repositories and adding a judgment category could be beneficial, along with updating the report headings. I wonder if I should run one round without external connections, especially if the script sends updates. It's essential to avoid sending duplicate messages externally. I should also ensure the LaunchAgent still runs daily at 09:00, with no changes needed there.\n\n**Designing configuration updates**\n\nI need to think about designing config entries with an \"exclude_from_report\" feature if we're going to keep scanning without reporting updates. The user mentioned they don’t need updates for this repo next time, so removing it from repos.json could help. If I remove the daily_stock_analysis_upstream, it won't get scanned at all. I should also make updating recommendations explicit, like \"强烈建议更新\" or \"可按需更新.\" Adding a new helper function for assessing update values sounds good, but it would require code changes.\n\n**Simplifying script changes**\n\nI'm considering that for the large script changes, I could simplify the \"should_update\" function to still return a tuple but with the reason phrased more explicitly along with a verdict. For example, if there are breaking changes, it could say “值得更新：包含 Breaking Changes...”. For 10 or more commits, it could say “值得更新：落后 X...”, and for 5-9, it might be “建议更新：...”. Finally, for 1-4 commits, it could read “可按需更新：...”. This should make things clearer!\n\n**Adjusting configuration settings**\n\nI’m considering how to best manage updates in my system. Instead of using \"建议,\" I can label the report lines as `- 更新判断：{reason}`. It’s crucial to ensure that local changes are counted properly. I’m also thinking about filtering out excluded repositories in the build summary, possibly by removing them from the configuration. If auto-discovery is still active for these repositories, they might reappear. So, I need a solid strategy to handle this effectively.\n\n**Managing excluded items**\n\nI’m thinking about how to maintain a list of dictionaries where excluded items have `\"enabled\": false` and a reason like `\"derived_from_daily_stock_analysis.\"` When loading configuration, I need it to respect these disabled items by excluding them from auto-discovery merging. This way, I’m preserving the user's preferences. I’ll implement logic to add paths to a disabled set when they're marked false, skip them during discovery, and update `repos.json` appropriately. I might also add a note for inventory updates.\n\n**Updating configuration logic**\n\nI’m focusing on making sure my update reasons are clear and explicit. I might rename the helper function, but I’m not entirely sure—it could go either way. In the report line, I'll include `- 更新判断：{reason}` in the update section. I need to be careful not to mention excluded repositories since the configuration skips those. When updating `repos.json`, I should decide to either include the disabled entries or remove them entirely. The active count will be 20 with 2 disabled at the end.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0faca0e75e9e48550169cdc6e16870819aa22c7027c77364e4\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpzcb2weB8FuMbH0r5Ez8cUwMEYB5M1m_Z6bBznMA4AEHA2X0_Woof4Be7SEzgkwaPKBovJo1jr5vhGVcrs8_ZOdy-fB4xY-lFfe_oYQxuS28X24uz4uUhtZEiscLzgQcMaKOSy689poXNl4P4UxCMb_1H0cErOON0fuCvvkyhkhQ8Lae0C6HIjvqxuUvFIQyD2lU6mC3unKPcJnT8Y3dFFy8cOOt4_p9SurQ208X_q7B8gdE8RE-k4EC6G64OZmK25lcDHz31IaVyNBWL1RIKSr-tB-r4YDoNuMV6qQLpOfNvMCXRzfxlrSe_h52Z2FdU86PnrV-SkPW3cd1hhEoPYHej5ZucGV1KwAE8_3JOgnWoJc5aRino3PnidK38VxHw6LzrK7_oWQt8vLLHpwuzrvNyJnK7QGLJMVD0bEZ7Ua2W4XxTywfcYt9-qteTTJ0jLlp_Z-EpZOEz-25qFEprqp4YOoHlZAz4FK4EnY8XqPjCE-0nIDhVSHupRJ1wBlHe5Fewfg3M