{"type":"message","id":"d5dfba53","parentId":"e22108f3","timestamp":"2026-04-02T06:57:49.215Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user said \"修吧\" (fix it) in response to the buy candidates issue. But which specific issue? Looking at the conversation context:\n\n1. The \"same as yesterday\" issue for defensive盘 is indeed a problem - the candidates are literally identical\n2. The aggressive盘 has NO candidates today (empty file)\n3. The balanced盘 did change\n\nThe user seems to want me to investigate WHY the defensive盘 candidates are identical between yesterday and today, and fix the underlying problem.\n\nI should:\n1. Investigate WHY the defensive盘 candidates are identical (is the chain not running? is it using stale data?)\n\n\n2. Look into the root cause - the signal generation pipeline might not be pulling fresh market data, or the strategy itself could be producing the same signals with identical parameters across both days\n3. Narrow down whether this is a data freshness issue or a logic problem in how the signals are being generated\n\nThe real question is whether the system is actually running the full pipeline today and getting real results, or if it's somehow recycling yesterday's outputs.\n\nLooking at the timestamp on the defensive盘 file, it was generated today at 09:47, so the pipeline did execute. The identical candidates suggest the strategy is consistently identifying the same stocks given similar market conditions, which could indicate the strategy itself is overly rigid or there's genuine stability in the signals. However, since I don't have direct access to the system's configuration, I need to first verify whether the system is actually configured to auto-refresh daily or if it's relying on stale data.","thinkingSignature":"69a5855d7ba65568406713895dbf7e51b98dd506bf39810db3a4da5df3b2cf1a"},{"type":"text","text":"收到，我直接查根本原因——为什么防御盘连续两天候选完全一样。\n\n先看看今天跑的时候用的持仓和实时数据源有没有更新。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fu