{"type":"message","id":"5b19f327","parentId":"cd52bf87","timestamp":"2026-04-02T13:04:41.148Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so:1. The apps/ directory versions of A_Share_investment_Agent, Qbot, RD-Agent, TrendRadar are **empty directories** - no content at all. These are dead symlinks or empty folders.\n2. `FileOrganizer.spec` is just a spec file, probably irrelevant\n3. `openclaw_projects/skills` contains installed skills (a-stock-monitor, agent-browser, akshare-finance, api-gateway, auto-updater, automation-workflows, capability-evolver, clawsec, ddg-web-search, find-skills, etc.)\nNow let me check which skills are actually from openclaw_projects/skills vs the main skills directory. The `openclaw_projects/skills` seems to be a parallel skills installation.\n\n\nSo these empty directories in apps/ are just clutter that should be cleaned up. For the active projects, Agent-Reach has significant local development with 102 commits ahead, and Wyckoff-Analysis is also actively developed with 120 commits ahead.\n\nLooking at the rest: TrendRadar is actively used in intelligence reports, while fireclawl and kkclaw are both experimental projects without git tracking and haven't been updated in a long time. SwarmMemory and openclaw-pet-shufanli are synced with remote. openclaw-control-center shows active development with 44 local commits. The stock_analysis_web project appears to be abandoned or just static files. For kids-box-tv-app, I need to check the git history to see how recently it's been worked on.\n\nFor the recommended deletions, fireclawl and kkclaw are definitely dead projects with no git history and no clear purpose. The empty directories in apps/ for A_Share_investment_Agent, Qbot, RD-Agent, and TrendRadar are just wasting space. The stock_analysis_web needs verification, but it looks like an old abandoned web interface. The skills folder under openclaw_projects is puzzling since it seems to be a mix of scripts rather than actual skills—that needs investigation. The 2023-2024 timestamps on fireclawl and kkclaw are concerning, so I should dig deeper into their actual content and creation dates before making final recommendations.","thinkingSignature":"0ccb6f03a7884998f53df0bf358ec9de5542f41ff012b0f55d96a631b8328bf3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0nsoavgucdsp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# fireclawl 和 kkclaw 的创建时间和内容规模\nfor d in /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/openclaw_projects/fireclawl \\\n         /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/openclaw_projects/kkclaw \\\n         /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/other_projects/stock_analysis_web; do\n  echo \"=== $(basename $d) ===\"\n  ls \"$d\" 2>/dev/null | head -10\n  find \"$d\" -type f 2>/dev/null | wc -l | xargs echo \"file_count:\"\n  find \"$d\" -type d 2>/dev/null | wc -l | xargs echo \"dir_count:\"\ndone","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":15}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0nsoavgucdsp_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# kids-box-tv-app 的 git 情况\ngit -C /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/other_projects/kids-box-tv-app log --oneline -1 2>/dev/null || echo NO_GIT\ngit -C /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/other_projects/kids-box-tv-app remote -v 2>/dev/null","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48646,"output":785,"cacheRead":25640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75071,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775135057791,"responseId":"061d9c52f405bcb912cd4d76826cf254"}}
